In a press briefing, President Biden stated that there have been no updates on the situation in Ukraine, and that there has been no change in the posture of Russian forces. He emphasized that if Russia were to invade Ukraine, there would be severe consequences, including economic sanctions and the reinforcement of NATO troops in Eastern Europe. President Biden also mentioned that he would personally sanction President Putin if he were to invade Ukraine. He stated that the deployment of the 8,500 troops on high alert would depend on Putin's actions. The President reassured NATO allies that the alliance would come to their defense if necessary. He acknowledged that it is difficult to predict Putin's intentions but warned of significant consequences if Russia were to invade Ukraine. President Biden also mentioned the possibility of a stable and predictable relationship with Russia but indicated that it remains to be seen.